CIDR:
=====

    - Classless Inter Domain Routing
    - Used when we have Security Groups for AWS Networking in General


    Two components:
    ===============

    - base IP (xxx.xxx.xxx.xxx)
    - Subnet Mask (/26)


    /32 - 2 power 0


    Quick Memo:
    ===========

    /32 - No IP can change
    /24 - Last IP number can change
    /16 - Last 2 can change
    /8 - Last 3 can change 
    /0 - all can change


    Exercise:
    =========


    192.168.0.0/24  => 192.168.0.0 - 192.168.0.255 (256)
    192.168.0.0/16  => 192.168.0.0 - 192.168.255.255 (65,536)
    192.0.0.0/8  => 192.0.0.0 - 192.255.255.255 (65,536)
    192.168.1.10/32  => 192.168.1.10 (1)
    0.0.0.0/0 - All IPs

    Private vs Public IPs:
    ======================

    10.0.0.0 - 10.255.255.255 (10.0.0.0/8) => Big Networks => Private Networks
    172.16.0.0 - 172.31.255.255 (172.16.0.0/12) => Default AWS One
    192.168.0.0 - 192.168.255.255 (192.168.0.0/16) => Home Networks


    All the rest of the IP on the internet are public IP

    

